    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> is the main way .NET applications work with databases</li>
            <li><strong>DbContext</strong> is your gateway to the database - it manages connections and operations</li>
            <li><strong>DbSet</strong> properties represent database tables and allow you to query data</li>
            <li><strong>Migrations</strong> track changes to your database schema over time</li>
            <li>Always call <strong>SaveChanges()</strong> after modifying data to persist changes</li>
            <li>Use <strong>LINQ queries</strong> (Where, OrderBy, Select) to filter and sort data</li>
            <li><strong>Connection strings</strong> tell EF Core how to connect to your database</li>
